16 WHEREAS, the enduring words etched above the theatre's iconic entrance—"A
17 MONUMENT DEVOTED TO THE BEST IN MUSIC PHOTOPLAY AND THEATRICAL
18 ARTS"—continue to reflect the Strand's mission and impact; and
19 WHEREAS, in its 90th year, the Strand remains a cornerstone of the Marietta arts scene, an
20 educational partner to local schools and organizations, and an economic engine for the city's
21 thriving downtown, drawing tens of thousands of visitors each year; and
22 WHEREAS, it is fitting and proper to commend the Earl and Rachel Smith Strand Theatre
23 for its remarkable legacy and ongoing contributions to the cultural, artistic, and civic life of
24 the State of Georgia.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
26 the members of this body honor the 90th anniversary of the Earl and Rachel Smith Strand
27 Theatre; extend their sincerest gratitude to its board, staff, volunteers, and supporters; and
28 encourage all Georgians to take part in celebrating this milestone and preserving its legacy
29 for future generations.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
32 Earl and Rachel Smith Strand Theatre.
